original: Lindqvist, Axel Albert, riksdagsman, riksgäldsfullmäktig, Halmstad, f. 23/ 10/78 i Kosta, Kronob. 1., av Joh. Alfr. L. o. Ida Augusta Åstrand. G. 09 m. Ester Elmgren. Barn: Ivar, Brita, Eric. — Ordf. i Glasarb. samorg. flera år, landstingsman sed. 10, led. av riksd. andra kamm. 11-20 o. sed. 22, led. av första lagutsk., utriutsk. o. utr:nd, led. av strafflagskomm. o. komm. f. ung-d :brottsligh. bekämp., led. av socrdem. grupp. förtr:råd, sekr. i socidem. riks-digrupp., v. ordf. i Sv:es stadshypo-tekskassa, led. av processlagberedn. rådgiv, nd, deleg. f. riksd. verk, led. av 21 års komm :skattekomm. o. statsrev. 20, 22, 23 o. 24, v. ordf. 23 o. 24, riksgäldsfullm. fr. 33, v. ordf., led. av hypotekssakk. 33 o. av domareut-brldn :sakk. 43, flera komm. uppdr.
translated: Lindqvist, Axel Albert, member of parliament, national debt commissioner, Halmstad, born on October 23, 1878 in Kosta, Kronoberg County, firstborn of Johannes Alfred Lindqvist and Ida Augusta Åstrand. Married in 1909 to Ester Elmgren. Children: Ivar, Brita, Eric. — Chairman of the Glassworkers' Trade Union for several years, county council member since 1910, member of the second chamber of parliament from 1911 to 1920 and since 1922, member of the First Committee on Legislation, Foreign Affairs Committee, and Justice Commission, member of the Criminal Law Commission and Commission for Combating Youth Crime, member of the Social Democratic Advisory Group, secretary of the Social Democratic National Executive Group, vice-chairman of the Swedish City Mortgage Bank, member of the Advisory Committee on Process Law, delegate for government agencies, member of the 21-year Tax Commission and State Audit in 1920, 1922, 1923, and 1924, vice-chairman in 1923 and 1924, national debt commissioner from 1933, vice-chairman and member of the Mortgage Commission in 1933, and member of the Judicial Training Commission in 1943, held several municipal assignments.

structured.description: Axel Albert Lindqvist was a Swedish politician and member of parliament. He served as the national debt commissioner and was born on October 23, 1878, in Kosta, Kronoberg County, Sweden. He was the firstborn of Johannes Alfred Lindqvist and Ida Augusta Åstrand. Axel Albert Lindqvist was married to Ester Elmgren in 1909 and had three children: Ivar, Brita, and Eric. He held various positions within the Glassworkers' Trade Union and was a member of the Social Democratic Party. Throughout his career, Axel Albert Lindqvist served on multiple committees and commissions, including the second chamber of parliament, the First Committee on Legislation, the Foreign Affairs Committee, the Justice Commission, the Criminal Law Commission, and the Commission for Combating Youth Crime.
